{
  "id": 5126896685809664,
  "name": "IndexedDB: SQLite backend (in-memory contexts)",
  "summary": "Chromium's IndexedDB implementation is rewritten on top of SQLite, to replace the previous implementation that uses a hybrid of LevelDB and flat files. There is no change to the Web API.\n\nThis is expected to improve reliability and, to a lesser extent, performance.\n\nFor now this is applied only to in-memory contexts such as Incognito mode in Chromium and Google Chrome. This limits the impact of any new bugs, as well as puts off the need to worry about migration of existing data persisted to disk.",
