  "automation_spec": false,
  "interop_compat_risks": "Interop: this work entails a web-visible behavioral change concerning an edge case in IDB transaction scheduling. This change brings Chromium in line with Firefox and Safari. (Both new and old behavior are standards-compliant.) See demo.\n\nCompatibility: This PSA exists primarily to warn of the risk of unintended breakage. The later step where persisted databases are stored with SQLite, and existing data is migrated to SQLite, will have higher associated risks and will have its own PSA.",
  "all_platforms": true,
  "all_platforms_descr": null,
  "non_oss_deps": null,
  "anticipated_spec_changes": null,
  "security_risks": "All data on disk is still segregated by storage bucket (origin).\n\nBoth new and old implementation are newly fuzz-tested.",
